# Documentation Governance Rules

## 400_ Guide Integration
- **NO NEW GUIDE FILES**: All content must fold into existing 400_ guides
- **Anchor System**: Use `<!-- ANCHOR_KEY: ... -->` for content organization
- **Priority Anchors**: Use `<!-- ANCHOR_PRIORITY: ... -->` for importance
- **Role Pins**: Use `<!-- ROLE_PINS: [...] -->` for role-specific content

## Cross-Reference Maintenance
- Update cross-references between related sections
- Maintain table of contents (TOC) when adding content
- Follow `200_naming_conventions` for headings and file naming
- Update any 400_ index/TOC doc when modifying content

## Documentation Hierarchy
- **HIGH Priority**: `100_memory/100_cursor-memory-context.md`, `400_guides/400_system-overview.md`
- **MEDIUM Priority**: `000_core/001_create-prd.md`, `000_core/002_generate-tasks.md`, `000_core/003_process-task-list.md`
- **LOW Priority**: `100_memory/100_backlog-guide.md`

## Content Organization
- Prefer updating canonical 400_ docs with anchors
- Cross-link updated sections and update any 400_ index/TOC doc
- Follow `200_naming_conventions` for headings, code fences, and file naming
- No new guide .md merges without an approved exception

## Quality Standards
- All documentation must follow markdown standards
- Each document must have a single h1 title matching filename
- TL;DR section required at top of core docs
- Cross-references must be maintained between related files